  <article>
    <h1>AI transparency</h1>
    <p>Hi, I'm the sole author of this blog. To maintain trust and transparency, here is exactly how I use LLMs in my content creation process.</p>

    <h2>How I use LLMs</h2>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Outlining</strong>: brainstorming structures for complex technical topics.</li>
      <li><strong>Proofreading</strong>: fixing typos, correcting grammar, and improving sentence flow.</li>
      <li><strong>Text styling</strong>: refining tone and formatting for better readability.</li>
      <li><strong>Code snippets</strong>: creating example code for the blog posts.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>What I don't do</h2>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>No ghostwriting</strong>: I don't auto-publish LLM text. Every article is written and reviewed by me.</li>
      <li><strong>No fake opinions</strong>: all viewpoints, architectural decisions, and tool evaluations are strictly my own.</li>
    </ul>
  </article>
